    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential integer underflow in count_nack_missing_parts function\n\n### Summary\nThe `count_nack_missing_parts` function in the RLC AM entity can experience integer underflow when processing PDU segments with negative `so` (segment offset) values or when calculating `new_last_byte` with malformed segment parameters. This can lead to incorrect missing part counts and potentially cause the RLC entity to generate malformed status PDUs with incorrect NACK information.\n\nThe issue manifests when the gNB receives PDU segments from UEs with corrupted or maliciously crafted RLC headers. Under certain conditions, this can cause the gNB to incorrectly report missing segments, leading to unnecessary retransmissions or, in extreme cases, RLC entity stall due to inconsistent state.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity_am.c`: Added bounds checking for `so` values and `new_last_byte` calculations in `count_nack_missing_parts` to prevent integer underflow.\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity_am.c`: Updated function comment to better document the return value semantics.\n\n"
}